<figureCitation box="[865,999,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[226,1373,208,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[197,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 25. Darwallia spp. 22 — D. barbata sp. n., holotype, female, in dorsal view; 23 — same, in frontal view; 24 — same, in lateral view; 25 — D. patula (Walker), male, in frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231556/files/figure.png" pageId="5">
Figs 
<number box="[924,999,1731,1755]" pageId="5" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1076,1730,1755]" name="India" pageId="5">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings, abdominal sternites IV- VII, and gonoplacs dark brown. Spines, claws, and horn-shaped processes of sternum VII black.
</paragraph>
